  <div class="col-md-8">
    
    <div class="bs-callout bs-callout-danger">
      <h4><b>Input</b></h4>
      <p>This is the address of the wallet that is sending the bitcoins.</p>
      <p class="highlight">Rememeber - the wallet is essentially just a record of all transactions it has been involved in. So, your wallet must have received the number of bitcoins you are trying to send (or more).</p>
    </div>
	
    <div class="bs-callout bs-callout-success">
      <h4><b>Amount</b></h4>
      <p>The number of bitcoins to be transferred. The most frequent denominations for bitcoin are:</p>
      
      <div class="highlight">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-2">milli-bitcoin (mBTC)</div>     
          <div class="col-md-2">0.001 BTC</div>     
        </div>
        
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-2">micro-bitcoin(Î¼BTC)</div>     
          <div class="col-md-2">0.000001 BTC)</div>     
        </div>
        
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-2">satoshi(sat.)</div>     
          <div class="col-md-2">0.00000001 BTC)</div>     
        </div>
      </div>
      
    </div>
	
    <div class="bs-callout bs-callout-warning">
      <h4><b>Output</b></h4>
      <p>This is the address of the receiving wallet.</p>
      <p class="highlight">In other words, this transaction will be added to the record of the wallet.</p>
    </div>
    
